Purpose: To tell the game engine exactly which piece of data to load next when a choice is made.
Example: If the player clicks a choice, the engine looks at the Node ID linked to that button and jumps to that specific point in the code.
Stability: Once you've linked a choice to a Node ID, you generally shouldn't change the ID name, or the "link" will break and the game won't know where to go. 
