Powering the "Pikaverse" Narrative
In a treasure hunt platform, these two elements manage the "flow" of the adventure:
Choice Text (The Clue/Action): This is where you’ll put your riddles or navigation options.
Example: "Solve the riddle of the Stone Arch" or "Head North toward the Whispering Woods."
Role: It keeps the player immersed in the Lucky Pikas world without them seeing the technical "gears" turning.
Node IDs (The Destination): These act as the "GPS coordinates" of your story tree.
Example: When a player chooses to solve the riddle, the game jumps to Node_ID: Arch_Puzzle_Success.
Role: This ensures that if you decide to rewrite a clue (Choice Text) later to make it harder or more "Pika-themed," the underlying hunt logic remains perfectly intact. 
