Since you're refining the platform now, consider these best practices for treasure hunt structures:
Clue Chaining: Use your Node IDs to build a sequence where finding one "treasure" (or solving one branch) unlocks the ID for the next stage.
Fail States vs. Re-routing: In branching narratives, you can have "dead-end" Node IDs that loop players back to a previous hint if they make the wrong choice, rather than ending the game entirely.
Unique ID Generation: To avoid bugs in a large Pikaverse, use a consistent naming convention for your Node IDs (like LVL_1_CLUE_A) or an ID generator to keep them unique across different hunts. 
